cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a new method for learning meta-embeddings, which involves unsupervised learning and linear algebra. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several NLP tasks, including semantic similarity, relation classification, and short-text classification, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
